The '''island whistler''' ('''''Pachycephala phaionota''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Pachycephalidae]] native to the [[Moluccas]] and islands of [[Western New Guinea]]. Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical dry [[forest]]s and subtropical or tropical mangrove forests.

The island whistler was originally described in the genus ''Myiolestes'' (a synonym for ''[[Colluricincla]]'').

